<%- include('../../shared/includes/head', {pageTitle: 'All products'}) %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/products.css" />
<script src="/scripts/cart-management.js" defer></script>
<%- include('../../shared/includes/head-end') %>

<body>
  <%- include('../../shared/includes/header') %>
  <main>
    <div class="splash">
      <h1>What's going on here?</h1>
      <p>
        A basic shop demo built in Node, Express and MongoDB. The database lives
        on MongoDB Atlas.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="splash">
      <h2>Things you can do:</h2>
      <h3>As an unregistered Customer:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Browse and add items to your shopping cart.</li>
        <li>View the cart, update item totals.</li>
        <li>Register!</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>As a registered and logged-in customer:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>All of the above, plus:</li>
        <li>
          Check out your cart via Stripe (use dummy card no. 4242 4242 4242 424,
          any email, any future expiry date, any CCV).
        </li>
        <li>Review your previous orders after checkout.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>As an Administrator:</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>
          Add, delete and update products (The first 3 products are protected
          from deletion)
        </li>
        <li>Review and change status of customer orders.</li>
        <li>(user: boss@cabstores.com, password: test123)</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        For full details on what is going on under-the-hood, please see the
        <a href="https://github.com/bauerindustries/shop-demo-project"
          >Readme</a
        >
        in the Github project repository.
      </p>
      <div id="splash-footer">
        <p>
          <a href="/products" class="btn btn-add">Let's go shopping...</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('../../shared/includes/footer') %>
</body>
